Definition.WordDefinition: Kiddy \Kid"dy\, n. A young fellow; formerly, a low thief. [Slang, Eng.] [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Kiddy \Kid"dy\, v. t. To deceive; to outwit; to hoax. [Slang] --Dickens. [1913 Webster]
